(192, 1, '2016-11-20 13:37:03', '2016-11-20 13:37:03', 'India folks freaking out about an Indian Marriage which is assumed to have spent a hefty sum of 73.5 million dollars at a phase where people are spending 4-5 hours approx. just to make a transaction of 2000-2500 Rupees by dint of standing in a long queue just to fulfill the starving needs of their family. I myself feel ashamed hearing this and I felt like being bullied by some filthy rich politicians who dont give a damn about people starving around them.\n\nGali Janardhan Reddy, a politician cum mafia of illegal mining who spent around 3 years\n\n[caption id="attachment_171" align="alignnone" width="514"]<a href="http://www.maikalaal.com/people-fuming-india-marriage-cost-73-5-million-phase-financial-crisis/800x480_image60334845/" rel="attachment wp-att-171"><img class=" wp-image-171" src="http://www.maikalaal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/800x480_IMAGE60334845-300x168.jpg" alt="common mob outraged with this lavish marriage" width="514" height="288" /></a> common mob outraged with this lavish marriage[/caption]\n\nin Jail for misusing his VIP power for personal benefits. Mr. Reddy spent a lavish amount of money to prosperously carry out the wealthy wedding of her daughter with an invitation to feed up around 50,000 people which is not tolerable to any Indian citizen who are standing resembling a clown just to take out his hard earned day- night money. Demonetisation is a good step, but my questions to some of the muddy &amp; corrupt politician is how can they ever consider of doing this?\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe wedding arrangement was colossal s hell to easily serve 50,000 people and they made a luxurious palace with an exact replica of a UNESCO world heritage site and few blocks away people were standing in long queues to just withdraw a small sum of money in front of ATMs were people were quarrelling and speaking shit to each other for getting their in hand cash first.\n\nIt was a shock for a common mob that how Mr